 With a Level 5 Craftbot you gain accress to the Filter Option. The Upgrade Button is Used for that.

f285b388-b132-4a5e-af2d-dbf920b7950b.description:
Default mode (night) active between 20:00 and 6:00, second mode (raidTime) active between 23:30 and 4:30. You need a logic gate in between if you want to power other components. 
Made by 00Fant
f285b388-b132-4a5e-af2d-dbf920b7950b.title: Daylight Sensor

b99153cf-1ddd-4c00-ab4e-f59c4c41dde3.description:
Can Grab Stuff. Not Units. Connect A Switch or Logic to turn it On. Connect a Red and Blue painted Logic to change the Distance by Inputs. Press (U) to change the filter Mode. Only In Creative it has Robots as Filter too! 
Made by 00Fant
b99153cf-1ddd-4c00-ab4e-f59c4c41dde3.title: Suckomatic

76762d72-01c0-47ae-8f3f-69cc39a529ec.description:
Detects dropped items in a box of 10x10x10 units around it (~ 32 blocks), matching the item in its filter slot. You need a logic gate in between if you want to power other components. 
Made by 00Fant
76762d72-01c0-47ae-8f3f-69cc39a529ec.title: Item Detector

edc811c8-9f43-4e34-b621-d2a43cc1497a.description:
A Chest with an integrated filter. Works like a normal chest if no filter is set. Activate it with a trigger to make it drag the filter item out of the connected tube system. 
Made by 00Fant
edc811c8-9f43-4e34-b621-d2a43cc1497a.title: Smart Chest

c4cf5661-f6a3-4720-9f71-7ccf3b22c667.description:
A cannon that shoots explosive canisters. Connect a trigger and an Explosive Boom Box (ammo box) to it. Small canister = short range, large canister = long range. 
Made by 00Fant
c4cf5661-f6a3-4720-9f71-7ccf3b22c667.title: Tank Cannon

557c1087-9023-476f-b5b4-80f0a8a17ce3.description:
The ammo box for the Tank Cannon. Small explosive canisters for short range shots, large explosive canisters for long distances. 
Made by 00Fant
557c1087-9023-476f-b5b4-80f0a8a17ce3.title: Explosive Boom Box

3cfddced-fc47-44fe-9881-9eeb2816c499.description:

Made by 00Fant
3cfddced-fc47-44fe-9881-9eeb2816c499.title: Mountable Shotgun

c4d9b90f-87b7-472b-b5a0-89920dd6d3dd.description:
If a robot is in range of both you and the detector, you will see the robot's name. If any Robot is in Range, the Robot Detector Returns a Logic Output ( on/off ). Use this to turn On/Off Unitfacer for example. 
Made by 00Fant
c4d9b90f-87b7-472b-b5a0-89920dd6d3dd.title: Robot Detector

Made by 00Fant
25257bb9-5322-47d9-8d82-91a424665df8.title: Icon Frame

6ccda6ba-f97d-485f-8bcf-6fd47d35dcbb.description:
It shoots the same chemical cloud like farmbots do. It's rather a PvP weapon, since robots dont care about chemicals. 
Made by 00Fant
6ccda6ba-f97d-485f-8bcf-6fd47d35dcbb.title: Chemical Cannon

Made by 00Fant

Made by 00Fant
0e16480c-697c-4511-9f7f-0656012bda72.title: Seat Input Converter

This block activates if it tilts down. The tip of the arrow is the front, the rest is the top side. You can Connect One Angle Sensor as input to Gyros. Connect a Switch (logic) to it. Active Input = Anglesensor Off.

48b2aeca-8a51-4a42-8577-0b3b7f1ab9b5.title: Angle Sensor

979b2a00-dbc4-4275-8fd6-1afb5933d383.description:
This is a Sensor that Will Aim with Bearings at Units or Soils.
It needs a Input Signal like a Button or logic gate to turn it On and 2 Bearings.
The Horizontal Axis bearing Must be the Default Color 
and the Vertical bearing must be any other color.
Then the Unit Facer knows What Bearings is for Up/Down and for Left/Right.

A battery container is now required too! Connect it to the Unit Facer!

The Color of the input button/gate will define what Targets it will choose.

DEFAULT Color = Only Robots
WHITE Color = All Units
BLUE Color = Wocs and Glowbugs
RED Color = Players
YELLOW Color = All Except Players!
BLACK Color = Other Players and not the Player Owner!
PURPLE Color = Aim at the Owner Aim Direction!
PINK Color = Aim at the Owner Aim Position!
GREEN Color = Aim At Soils Without Plants!
DARKGREEN Color = Aim At Soils Without Grown Plants!
LIGHTBLUE Color = Aim At Soils With Plants and NO Water!
LIGHTORANGE = Aim at Rocks!
LIGHTYELLOW = Aim at Trees!
LIGHTGREEN = Aim at RefineRods
BROWN = Block Target
LIGHTGRAY = Waypoint Follow
DARKGRAY = Droped Item Target

Multiple inputs possible, only one signal turns the Unit Facer on
Press (U) to set yourself as Owner.
Made by 00Fant
979b2a00-dbc4-4275-8fd6-1afb5933d383.title: Unit Facer

109c422b-764b-4993-9f4a-50a45c3160be.description:
Its a Fridge.
A refrigerator (colloquially fridge) is a home appliance consisting of a thermally insulated compartment and a heat pump (mechanical, electronic or chemical) that transfers heat from its inside to its external environment so that its inside is cooled to a temperature below the room temperature. Refrigeration is an essential food storage technique in developed countries. The lower temperature lowers the reproduction rate of bacteria, so the refrigerator reduces the rate of spoilage. A refrigerator maintains a temperature a few degrees above the freezing point of water. Optimum temperature range for perishable food storage is 3 to 5 C (37 to 41 F).[1] A similar device that maintains a temperature below the freezing point of water is called a freezer. The refrigerator replaced the icebox, which had been a common household appliance for almost a century and a half.
109c422b-764b-4993-9f4a-50a45c3160be.title: Smart Fridge
